    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-13T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="190"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">641.116/2523: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-13T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 13, 1939—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 13—4:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2344. Embassy’s 2232, November 1, 1 p.m. Board of Trade advises that it expects
                    to announce Wednesday night a prohibition on all imports of apples and pears
                    shipped from the United States on and after November 20. The Board will advise
                    later the exact time when this information may be made public.</p>
                <p>Trade advises that Bank of England already refusing exchange for new orders.</p>
                <p>Advise Agriculture.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
